---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<DocsLayout title="Payload Sanitization" activeNav="sanitization" description="Automatic SQL injection detection and XSS stripping with recursive payload scanning.">

  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys automatically scrubs every incoming request payload for <strong>SQL injection</strong> and <strong>XSS</strong> attacks before your business logic executes. The sanitization middleware intercepts request bodies, query parameters, and headers — scanning them recursively through nested JSON structures.
  </p>

  <h2 id="detection-strategy">Detection Strategy</h2>
  <p>Araxys uses two different strategies depending on the attack type:</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attack Type</th>
        <th>Patterns</th>
        <th>Action</th>
        <th>HTTP Response</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>SQL Injection</strong></td>
        <td>16 regex patterns</td>
        <td><strong>Block</strong> — reject entire request</td>
        <td><code>400 Bad Request</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>XSS</strong></td>
        <td>9 regex patterns</td>
        <td><strong>Strip</strong> — remove malicious content via bleach</td>
        <td>Request proceeds (cleaned)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="alert alert--info">
    <div class="alert-title">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 16px;">info</span>
      Design Decision
    </div>
    <div class="alert-content">
      SQLi attempts are <strong>blocked entirely</strong> because they target your database — allowing a "cleaned" query through is too risky. XSS payloads are <strong>stripped</strong> because bleach can safely remove malicious HTML while preserving legitimate content.
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="sqli-patterns">SQL Injection Patterns</h2>
  <p>Araxys detects 16 SQLi patterns including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>UNION-based</strong>: <code>UNION SELECT</code>, <code>UNION ALL SELECT</code></li>
    <li><strong>Boolean-based blind</strong>: <code>OR 1=1</code>, <code>AND 1=1</code></li>
    <li><strong>Time-based blind</strong>: <code>SLEEP()</code>, <code>WAITFOR DELAY</code>, <code>BENCHMARK()</code></li>
    <li><strong>Stacked queries</strong>: <code>; DROP TABLE</code>, <code>; DELETE FROM</code></li>
    <li><strong>Comment injection</strong>: <code>--</code>, <code>/**/</code></li>
    <li><strong>Function abuse</strong>: <code>LOAD_FILE()</code>, <code>INTO OUTFILE</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="xss-patterns">XSS Patterns</h2>
  <p>Araxys detects and strips 9 XSS vectors:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Script tags</strong>: <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> in all variations</li>
    <li><strong>Event handlers</strong>: <code>onerror</code>, <code>onload</code>, <code>onclick</code>, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>JavaScript URIs</strong>: <code>javascript:</code> protocol</li>
    <li><strong>Data URIs</strong>: <code>data:text/html</code> payloads</li>
    <li><strong>Iframe injection</strong>: <code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code> tags</li>
    <li><strong>SVG/math payloads</strong>: <code>&lt;svg onload=...&gt;</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="recursive-scanning">Recursive Scanning</h2>
  <p>
    The scanner traverses nested JSON payloads recursively up to a configurable depth limit. This catches attacks hidden deep within nested objects:
  </p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">json</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code set:html={`{
  "user": {
    "profile": {
      "bio": "&lt;script&gt;alert('xss')&lt;/script&gt;"  <span class="token-comment">// ← caught at depth 3</span>
    }
  }
}`} /></pre>
  </div>

  <h2 id="configuration">Configuration</h2>

  <div class="code-block">
    <div class="code-block-header">
      <span class="code-block-lang">python</span>
      <button class="code-block-copy">Copy</button>
    </div>
    <pre><code><span class="token-keyword">from</span> araxys.core.config <span class="token-keyword">import</span> SanitizeConfig

config = <span class="token-function">AraxysConfig</span>(
    <span class="token-param">secret_key</span>=<span class="token-string">"..."</span>,
    <span class="token-param">sanitize</span>=<span class="token-function">SanitizeConfig</span>(
        <span class="token-param">enabled</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-param">block_sqli</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-param">strip_xss</span>=<span class="token-bool">True</span>,
        <span class="token-param">max_depth</span>=<span class="token-number">10</span>,
        <span class="token-param">exclude_paths</span>=[<span class="token-string">"/upload"</span>],  <span class="token-comment"># Skip file upload endpoints</span>
    ),
)</code></pre>
  </div>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Field</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>enabled</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Enable/disable sanitization</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>block_sqli</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Block SQL injection attempts</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>strip_xss</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Strip XSS payloads</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>block_nosqli</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Block NoSQL injection ($operators)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>block_cmdi</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Block command injection</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>block_path_traversal</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Block path traversal</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>max_depth</code></td><td><code>int</code></td><td><code>10</code></td><td>Max recursion depth for nested scanning (≥1)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>exclude_paths</code></td><td><code>list[str]</code></td><td><code>[]</code></td><td>Paths excluded from sanitization</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>scan_query_params</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>True</code></td><td>Scan query parameters</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>scan_headers</code></td><td><code>bool</code></td><td><code>False</code></td><td>Scan request headers</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="nosql-injection">NoSQL Injection</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys detects and blocks <strong>MongoDB $operator injection</strong> attacks. When <code>block_nosqli=True</code>, the scanner detects MongoDB operators including <code>$gt</code>, <code>$ne</code>, <code>$where</code>, <code>$regex</code>, <code>$nin</code>, <code>$exists</code>, <code>$gte</code>, <code>$lte</code>, and others. The request is rejected with <code>400 Bad Request</code> — fail-closed, identical to SQLi blocking.
  </p>

  <h2 id="command-injection">Command Injection</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys detects <strong>shell metacharacters</strong> and <strong>dangerous commands</strong> in request payloads. When <code>block_cmdi=True</code>, the scanner blocks shell metacharacters (<code>;</code>, <code>|</code>, <code>&amp;&amp;</code>, <code>||</code>, backticks <code>`</code>, <code>$()</code>) and dangerous commands (<code>rm</code>, <code>wget</code>, <code>curl</code>, <code>nc</code>, <code>bash</code>, <code>sh</code>, <code>powershell</code>). Returns <code>400 Bad Request</code>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="path-traversal">Path Traversal</h2>
  <p>
    Araxys detects <strong>directory traversal</strong> attempts. When <code>block_path_traversal=True</code>, the scanner blocks sequences including <code>../</code> and <code>..\\</code>, null bytes (<code>\0</code>), and absolute path references (<code>/etc/passwd</code>, <code>C:\</code>). Returns <code>400 Bad Request</code>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="extended-scanning">Extended Scanning</h2>
  <p>
    By default, Araxys scans the request <strong>body</strong> (JSON payload). The extended scanning options expand coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><code>scan_query_params</code></strong> (<code>True</code> by default): Scans query parameter <strong>names AND values</strong> for all injection types</li>
    <li><strong><code>scan_headers</code></strong> (<code>False</code> by default): Scans request headers for all injection types</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="alert alert--warning">
    <div class="alert-title">
      <span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 16px;">warning</span>
      Header Scanning Caution
    </div>
    <div class="alert-content">
      <code>scan_headers</code> is <strong>False by default</strong> — headers often contain base64-encoded content, JWT tokens, or API keys that may trigger false positive matches against injection patterns.
    </div>
  </div>

</DocsLayout>

</DocsLayout>
